ratings.rComments: He is the best math teacher at UIUC. He made calculus so clear. Definitely take his class if you have a chance. However, because math220 is a 5 credit course, and he had so many stuffs to teach. Some students might think his lectures are too fast. But if you pay attention you will be fine. And really recommend to the past exams and quiz.

Great note provider, as long as you take the notes well, you will totally be fine. You can basically copy whatever he writes on the blackboard cuz it includes everything!  Grading is super fair too. He replaces the final grade with one of your lowest midterms and still get to keep the final grade for final.
Amazing lecturer. Passionate about math. Drops lowest two quizzes and will replace your lowest exam score with your final score. The exams are VERY difficult. Be prepared.
The best professor I have met till now.
Just a great supporter and a really clear professor during lectures.
By far the best math teacher I have ever had. Fantastic lectures that are actually enjoyable, tests are fair.
The test can be super hard. Get ready to do lots of practice.

Professor Murphy is a phenomenal educator. He provides both the resources and the insight necessary to master the material he covers. In a broader sense, he has a certain way about him that makes learning the subject he teaches (calculus 1) feel a worthwhile endeavor.

Great teacher. Very patient whenever you went to him for a math problem, personal issue, or a regrade. His class is very easy to understand because he was using a very formal, standard way to break down every problem and those problems will appear in tests and quizzes, nothing unexpected. He also posts all previous tests online for you to practice.
Very clear explanations and teaching.

He has online quizzes and exams from past semesters. USE THEM. I never read a page from the text book and I understood the material very well because of past exams and quizzes. He is very  strict on grading but will make you think you rock at calc (until you get to calc 2 with horrible professors).

As someone who doesn't really like Math, Bob Murphy is the best Math Teacher/Professor I have ever had.  Although I did pretty average in this class grade wise, I felt I understood the material way better than I ever had before in any other math.  This class is a perfect example of you get out what you put in.

Bob was one of the best professors I ever had. His lectures were engaging and he gives students all of the tools they need in order to succeed in his class, so long as they access them first. It is also important to note that regular attendance at office hours greatly increases one's chances for success.

He is definitely the best teacher I've had so far in two years! I dreaded math but ended up actually understanding all the concepts. I was quite intimidated coming into class at first, but by the end of the semester I left feeling confident with calculus. He definitely prepares you well for further calculus courses. Do well on quizzes!
Awesome teacher overall. If you put in the time and effort, he'll definitely help you out at office hours. Great lectures and very easy to talk to, and his grading process is very lenient overall.

The best math teacher I have ever had. His explanations are very clear and he breaks down difficult concepts in ways that are  clear and understandable. However, he will make you work for your grade. I ended up with an A, but I had to put a lot of effort in. Definitely take Calc 1 with him if you truly want to understand the material.
The professor is a great person. He tries to make sure everyone who whats to succeed succeeds. But it is up to you on how much your willing to work. This class is a lot of work.
Great Lectures and Most of the tests weren't too bad at all just gotta do the work

He's the best math teacher I've ever had period. He is very clear and concise. One thing that I would advise is don't slack on quizzes. That probably killed my grade in the end. I got B's on the midterms with about 3 days of work but a D in my quiz section (which is worth 1 midterm altogether).

Easily the best math instructor I've had in my entire life. Explains things clearly and in a manner "a kindergartner could understand," which is how teaching should be done. Of course, have precalc taken care of before. Also, do the "optional" HW; without it, you will do poorly. Be prepped for time crunch quizzes and use the free math tutoring!

He's a pretty good professor. There were a lot of quizzes but there are old practice quizzes online that are the exact same. It is the same with tests. I haven't done any of the homework this semester and I am doing pretty decent because I go to my discussion and I take these practice quizzes/tests. I would recommend his class.

He is the best professor I can ever imagine!  He is good at clarifying ideas, so you will definitely understand every knowledge after the lecture.  In addition, he is ready to help, so feel free to email him anything that bothers you!  The tests are very easy as long as you do the old tests and quizzes!  Strongly recommended!!!
Hard but fair. Excellent lectures and very helpful outside of class.

A good math teacher is a very rare thing. Prof. Murphy is a teaching diamond in a lot of rough out there. I would've taken Math 220 online if I hadn't been able to get him. You'll do well only if you do the hw and go to lectures AND discussion.  Be prepped for the 15 min. quizzes. Also, do not take without prior calc or precalc (Math 115).

Not sure why this class has such high reviews. Lectures are difficult to understand as he flies through material. Tests and quizzes are impossible. Puts terribly intricate problems on tests and quizzes that make your head spin.

Love him so much!!! With an easygoing disposition .Explains calculus clearly in each lecture and has his own class Syllabus, which tells  what u r supposed to learn and what the tough part is in each lecture. Gives a guidance about what to read! Such an organized and inspirational guy!Take his class!
Great professor, but likes to test students on the intricacies that are conceptually difficult.

Murphy is a great professor! His explanation is very clear and easy to understand. You can find lots of practice exams and quizzes in his website and they're very similar to the actual exams and quizzes. Tests are not that hard as long as you put in effort to do the practice exams.

Okay, of all the things you take from this review, just remember - *Do the homework.* Seriously. He gives you all the tools to do well, and just doing the homework and checking it over will make your test and quiz grades skyrocket. I got a D in the class the first time because I didn't do the work. Took it again and got a B+. Fantastic professor.

Murphy is a great person and a great professor. Tests seemed almost impossible. My advice is if you took calc in high school you might be ok, but if you only took pre calc and no calc, take this class at a community college!

The tests and quizzes ain't easy but he provided a lot of resources which means, you just have to work for it. The office hours really helped a lot.  The textbook are only useful to complete the assigned homeworks (which I don't think are essential to pass the class). Just do all the past tests and quizzes and you'll be fine!

The thing about Bob is that he doesn't give homework because he feels you don't need it to pass his class. Attend all his lectures because he gives the hardest examples of problems you can encounter and then breaks them down. I enjoyed the class and got an easy A- simply because I diligently went to lecture. Office hours  aren't necessary

For many people (at least for me), Calculus is a scary thing. Professor Murphy does a great job with teaching the course material. Unfortunately, he is aware of this, so the test and quizzes can be quite difficult. Just make sure you do the non-mandatory HW. The Final replaces your lowest test grade so make sure you study A LOT for it.
I did not go to class and that hindered me a lot. Go to his personal office hours, I have not heard anything good about the TA's. Do the assigned book work for practice.
challenging class, skips steps, goes by to fast
Very fair but strict in grading. Can get an easy B just by going to lectures.

Very difficult class. Even taking and passing AP calc in high school, this class was 10x harder. Half the class dropped out by mid-semester. Average grade of all 3 tests were D's. Very tough grader.  He claims that doing the homework is essential for doing well, but the homework never helps on the tests. Dont take! Take at community college!

Murphy is the math teacher I have ever had. He is a great lecturer, you need to work hard for the grade, but if you stay up to date and attend class you will be good. His previous quizzes are almost identical to the ones he gives out now. The prior exams also help a lot. One of the best teachers in the math department. You Da man murphy

I was new to Calculus when I took this class, and he made it very easy to get into it. I was not going to class enough by the end of the semester, so I got a C. Probably would have gotten an A or B if I showed up.

This class really makes you work for your grade. MURPHY DOES NOT CURVE.  Even with a class average of 50 there was no curve all semester.  Take advantage of the practice quizzes and tests online, they prepare you well for the real ones.  Lecture and discussion are not mandatory but it is very beneficial to go, especially lecture. Office hours OK.
He's one of the best professor in Math department! Very patient and really helpful!!

his tests and quizzes are not  easy, but questions similar to those given in his tests are similar to those in his past quizzes and tests. you can do well by studying. he gives you all his exams and quizzes since 2009. he is nice and good at explaining stuff, he will make sure you get it. no mandatory attendance. good professor. i hate math btw

Solid teacher, but the material can get really abstract and makes you think. There isn't any assigned homework; the course grade is dependent on quizzes and tests so make sure to do all the homework even though it's not due for any points

Excellent teacher, don't take his course if you plan on being lazy or assume high school calc guarantees you an A. The material he teaches will show up on tests and definitely the methods and examples from lecture will help. Always great at answering questions. He wants you to learn and will help you get there. Don't fall behind.
I never really understood why I was taking Calculus, but Murphy was pretty good. The TAs are no help at all
Really a nice professor I've ever had. He's so patient to students.
Really love Professor Murphy. He is very funny, and the he can cover the material clearly. Best Math Professor ever,

Great Professor. Obviously very passionate about the subject and explains things amazingly. Very easy to get a hold of and get help.  The Quizzes are pretty hard I must say. The exams are pretty straight forward and he provides all past exams on his website dating back to almost 6 years ago.
Really helpful and easy course

One of the best calculus teachers I've had, started from the beginning and worked quickly but cleared everything up and I actually understood material instead of memorizing it. Amazing lectures and board work. Writes everything step by step. For quizzes and tests take advantage of all of the past quizzestests online - it's still a weed out class

Fantastic professor; the best I've had in the math department as of yet. His explanations were crystal clear and backed up with lots of example problems. Be warned though that his class is kind of tough. The quizzes are hard and worthy of being studied for. The tests are a bit easier but harder than the tests I took in Calc 2 and he doesn't curve.
Very fast paced with teaching, but very helpful. He wants his students to succeed. Go to office hours, I promise it helps. Also, make SURE to read the book. Plus, he's hot so take his class ;)

Murphy is one of those professors that obviously loves math. I like that he brought that passion to his lectures, making sure we really understand what's going on. He's my favorite calculus professor.
Good lecturer, very helpful. Can go through material quickly, but if you go to office hours you will be fine
Great prof and explains materials clearly!

He's really fair and the best math teacher I've ever had. If you have any problems go to office hours. He explains everything and anything you have questions about. His final also replaces your lowest test and I got a %56 on one test then got a %98 on the final so it definitely helps

He is awesome!!!!He explains everything really clear and the homework are useful. His lesson is really attractive and the professor himself is a very nice person!Don't know why his score is so low. Choose his class, you will love him!

Do not take this class if you are not an engineer or a math major. His class is based souly on those few students who just understand the material at the get go. Anyone who just needs this class to fill a requirement I recommend  finding another professor because you'll likely end up working your ass off 20+ hours a week just to fail.

Class is average in difficulty (I never took calc in high school). Murphy DOES NOT curve, instead he replaces your lowest test grade with the final %. He lets you view his previous Quizes and Tests. This significantly helps improve performance on exams. Final exam is a bit easier then the midterms.

Course is not hard because he explains everything clearly in his lecture. Also,during his office hours, your can ask him the questions on quizzes or homework, and he will explain every detail, even calculating.
Great teacher, he moves through a lot of material quickly but makes it seem simple and straightforward.
Best math professor I have ever had.

He's a great professor, lots of office hours, good at what he does, and no mandatory homework. He moves really fast. however. I strongly suggest going to office hours. He's a really nice guy and has a sense of humor. He also doesn't curve so be ready for those exams.

Miserable class, difficult material. Murphy is misleading with his lectures, and his exams rarely correlate to class. I would recommend another teacher or go to community college for calc if it is required.

He is one of the best proffesors I've ever had.  He has lots of office hours where he goes through confusing homework problem.  Also the tests are not that difficult as long as you have been doing all of the recomended homework problems and review guides.
Definitely the best Math teacher I've ever had. Believe me if u work hard in this class with his  teaching to help, u'll be fine.

Very good teacher. Extremely fair and helpful. The material is tough, but everything you need to know he clearly teaches in lecture. My TA was good too. Go to his office hours; he sincerely wants to help his students and will clearly answer any question you have. Use his website for old quizzes and tests, those help a lot.

Murphy is great, but the class itself is challenging. If you put in the time and effort, it will pay off. Do the homework and study. If you're confused, you can always approach him or go to office hours. It's also helpful to have a study buddy or a group.

His lectures are great! However, the hw load is a little bit too much. TA sessions are not all helpful. So choose a good TA! Overall, this is a very good cal1 class and really help you get prepared for cal2.

Terrible, difficult, and unforgiving in most respects. Think again if you don't have experience with calculus, because there are better suited classes with more compensating instructors in the same course.
no homework. no mandatory attendance. easy exams.

Crystal clear lectures. He makes sure you understand all formulas/theorems conceptually by deriving them in class. Some of my friends thought this was overkill, but I think it helps build a good foundation in the subject. It's not an easy class, but if you're willing to put in the work, you shouldn't have a problem getting the grade you want.

Overall, Murphy is a nice professor, but you HAVE to do his homework. I have never taken calculus before, so it was challenging. Got a D on the first exam, but ended up with a B in the class.He does throw tricky questions on the exam so be careful and make sure you understand every HW problem

OMG He's so enthusiastic about his job and he is definitely a good teacher! I didn't do much hw before mid-term cause I was struggling with my PSYC class so I got C, however I worked harder and ends up with an A!!!

Bob Murphy is truly a great lecturer. He is fantastic at explaining concepts and his in class examples were very helpful. Despite the fact that this is only Calc 1, it is not an easy class, but it is possible to get an A or B if you put in the time and do the homework. I came in with no prior calculus experience and received a B+.

This class is sooo fair. The grading system is perfect, and theres barely tricks on tests. Just do hw and listen to his words. Hes so chilllll so you can just stop by and be like whats up? hes so cool and you would wanna be friends with him. Everyone already is. I wish he taught all my classes!!

He is upbeat and wants students to learn, but this class is impossible for someone who struggles with math in the first place. It is five days a week and a ton of hw. And sometimes there are two quizzes in a week, tue and thurs. he said that most of those who fail the first test fail the course. Final can replace the lowest test but no curving.

Great Professor!  I took Calc in High School and did terrible, but I understood everything thanks to this man.  Very fair, MUST do the homework.  He is more than happy to help you outside of class as well.  His only downfall: breaks more chalk than any normal man ever could.

Professor Murphy is amazing. I was intimidated by calculus and maths but had to learn it as a requirement for my major but I attended his class and now I'm minoring in Maths. Great professor. Very passionate while teaching and is very helpful, always. I'll highly recommend anyone taking calculus to take his class.
He is really good. He love this job and clearly patient to his students. His the best math teacher I ever met. I like him.
Clear but not Helpful. Confused with problems himself sometimes. Tests are easy. Got perfect scores on all tests, quizzes, and finals.
His tests are usually straightforward and directly related to homework problems.  He does, however, grade with a straight scale, which many students considered an obstacle to good grades.

Math 220 is no doubt HARD. He's an amazing teacher though. To get the grade 1, DO ALL HOMEWORK, 2, REVIEW OLD TESTS AND QUIZES, 3, GO TO DISCUSSION. The final is the curve since it replaces your lowest test grade. Tests are tough but if you do your hwk and review old tests, you'll do fine. Be prepared to work for the A or B. Its doable though
straight scale grading is rough

Really hard class, if you've never taken calc before, I recommend doing all the homework despite having 30 problems every day as this is a 5 hour course, and not take the previous tests lightly as he increases the difficulty each semester for each test. Overall though, he is a nice and helpful teacher, but many people will end up with C's or D's.

Calc I was a very tough class as someone who has not taken a Calculus course before. Murphy did, however, do a great job of explaining concepts with well thought out examples. As long as one listens with intent during class and COMPLETES THE HOMEWORK, he or she should have no problem getting the desired grade.

This professor is all over the place. He doesn't explain anything and doesn't know how to do the problems himself. Just the other day he stopped explaining a problem on the board because he didn't know how to do it himself. You have to teach yourself the material. Good luck on the impossible tests. Honestly, I'm smart okay, but this prof is imposs.

Excellent professor! Probably the best you can get for math 241 (he only teached 1 class this time, and I was in it). Calc3 is a hard class, especially towards the end- but his explanations are great, so it'll help lots. grading is straightforward- solely based on quiz and tests, with no hw to hand-in <3 this helps me actually study and ace it.

By far the best math teacher I've ever had.  Every time he begins a new concept, he explains it thematically and concisely.  If you pay attention, you basically have no choice but to learn.  I went to a lot of his office hours, and if you ask the right questions, he will make you love calculus!

Professor Murphy is awesome! I am happy to have had him as a professor. He explains everything clearly and is always there for help. Attending lecture is not mandatory, but it is extremely helpful. Tests and quizzes are very similar to the old ones so study those and you should be fine.

Great professor. I came in with no prior calculus experience and found him very easy to understand. He does a great job of explaining. If you want to do well in the class make sure you do well on tests and overall well on the quizzes. He drops a few of the lowest quiz scores. VERY HELPFUL and uses LOTS OF EXAMPLES.

Perfect professor. Strongly recommend if you take math 220. Clear lectures, efficient, always ready to answer questions, humorous. 13 quizzes through the semester and you can drop 3 of them. 3 tests and a cumulative final, which means you can replace one of your test score by your final.
The course itself is esay. He doesn't ask for homework so I've never done any. Great lectures. He's a good teacher. Exams are easy. I got a B- by midterm and hold it back to A at the end.

Excellent Instructor. Clear and Concise. Keeping up on homework is a must, but the exams/quizzes aren't that difficult if you do the homework, and ask questions. Best U of I instructor I've had so far.

Professor SHINES!! I am the student I am today because of him. He will go out of his way to explain things, and will be the fairest man you will ever meet. I HIGHLY recommend him, and I hope he can have the impact he had on me with you. If you are frustrated, hang in there and fight fight fight! His policy allows you to prove yourself on the final!

He definitely knows the material really well. I highly recommend doing all the assigned homework even though it's not due. It can be a difficult class if you never had calculus before because the material moves pretty fast but as long as you keep up with the homework and attend lecture it is possible to get a decent grade. Also look at old quizzes.

Friendly professor, efficient teacher.  Willing to help if necessary. If you stay on top of the material, you'll do fine.  If you are having trouble, you can go to his office hours and he will gladly help.
Great Professor, one of the greatest teachers I've ever had, I recommend him to anyone who needs to take Calc!

He is awesome, soo easy to understand and explains everything he is doing, all the homework is optional, and he replaces your your worst test grade with the grade from your final (if its better so it will only help your grade)
He was an excellent professor and really made it so that you could understand clearly. The material is hard so GO TO OFFICE HOURS, I learned the hard way.
Murpheus = God walking among mortals who stretches squirrels in his leisure time...Take his class!!!!!

Calculus is not an easy subject! He taught, but I had to go over a lot of information on my own. Actually, he completely skipped a chapter and left it for the class to do on their own. The class isn't that bad, though.
I found myself enjoying math after having taken his class...I don't know how to feel about this.  Regardless, he's an excellent professor!

I failed the first 2 exams and got a C+. It is not easy to turn your grade around, but the key to success if your struggling is to seek help and ask pertinent questions. The points only come from exams, quizzes, and final. Start preparing early, exams are full of pressure. If you are mediocre at algebra, polish it because the penalty is harsh.
Excellent.

Professor Murphy is an awesome teacher. He is very clear in his teaching. His Calc 2 class is easier than calc 3. MAKE SURE TO DO THE HOMEWORK! Even though it isn't for a grade. His tests tend to stress the material covered in class, so make sure to attend all lectures.

Absolutely fantastic professor.  His lectures are crystal clear because he has is able to break concepts down and explain them logically.  He is very fair when it comes to quizzes/exams.  I took professor Murphy for both calc 1 and 2 and my only regret is that he isn't teaching calc 3.  In short, if you have the opportunity, take Bob Murhpy.
Make math interesting
Really good teacher. Exams were way easier than with other Math 231 professors. Definitely pick him over anyone else that I know of. He's very helpful and has a sense of humor.

EXCELLENT TEACHER!!!!! Best Experience that I had in my first semester of college with teachers. I'm so glad I ended up in his class. Very good at explaining the material. As long as you care about your grade, its impossible to do poorly in this class. AND HE'S SUPER NICE! :D
I LOVE HIM! He's such a nice professor! He explains things really clear, and the materials are really easy. Do old exams! they help a lot. I'm taking 231 with him this semester. Still love him!
kind and interesting

This course is extremely challenging for a student with average math skills. A's are only obtainable by students with natural born knowledge. I put in 15 hours a week and struggled quite a bit. Professor Murphy is outstanding however he will sometimes move very fast. More than clear in office hours, and teaches straight forward. exams never curved

During lecture he mostly just proves theorems, and he is very approachable in office hours.  Even though the homework isn't graded, keep on top of it and you'll do better on quizzes and exams.  All his old exams and quizzes are online, and he reuses the same type of questions.  This class is do or die. I was happy with my A-. Take it with Murphy.
He's a fantastic teacher. He teaches with such clarity that it's almost impossible not to understand the material. Love him!

Best math teacher that I have ever had. He loves his job and will do anything to help his students. Use his past tests to study because some questions will reappear. I highly recommend taking his class!
Love Bob! He is super nice, and those quizzes & tests r quite easy lol

He is a good teacher and always does a good job explaining the material in lecture. Some of the material you will completely understand in lecture but can be more puzzling when you look at it on your own. Overall very good prof. just be sure to study with old tests/quizzes.

He is a good teacher and always does a good job explaining the material in lecture. Some of the material you will completely understand in lecture but can be more puzzling when you look at it on your own. Overall very good prof. just be sure to study with old tests/quizzes.
Amazing professor. Teaches concepts extremely clearly. Grading is very fair.
Great Professor.  Fair grading scheme.  Understanding is taught by him, not just how to pass a test.
Murphy is really fun! His tests r usually not hard. Do his homework, and you'll get a easy A. recommended
Emphasis on understanding rather than just doing. Great professor.

This was an OK class for me; math is my weakest subject so I had to put in a lot of effort to get a B. Bob's a really good teacher - good lectures and explanations. He's incredibly fair (dropped quizzes, no mandatory homework, etc).
He was very clear in his explanations and very knowledgable about the subject. I figured that the class would be much more difficult than it is. I recommend him if you have to take calculus.

Gotta love bob! Although I got a C in this class and still am stumped about much of the material, he was a great professor. You could tell he was very interested in teaching and he even gave us candy on the day after halloween!!
this class is awful. he procrastinates on EVERYTHING, and clearly has no interest in teaching this class. i've heard he's good for calculus, but he's terrible for this.

my first calc class ever. He was very clear with explanations, otherwise he would go over again. He is very fair with the exam material and lets you drop enough quizzes and 1 exam so you can ace the course. If you want an A read the book and write down the examples he give in class.
He stresses notation a lot, which I wasn't expecting.  Exams are in class, and they're pretty thorough.  Not terribly hard, just thorough.  Do the homework, you'll be fine.

Personally, I dislike math (it's the subject I struggle most with), but I got the grade I expected. Bob's a really good & fair teacher. I learned much more from my TA though. This class shouldn't be too hard as long as you do the homework, go to the discussions, and ASK QUESTIONS!
